    What is a MIME type?

    A MIME type is a way of identifying files on the Internet according to their nature and format. Your server needs this information to determine what kind of file has been uploaded, otherwise it will reject the file.

    Upload a file to check its MIME type

    We've made it easy to figure out your file's MIME type. Upload any sample file below and click "Get MIME Type" and we will display the MIME type for that file. For example, if you wanted to check the MIME type for the .zip extension, you would need to upload any random ZIP file. Once we have determined the correct MIME Type, click to enter that MIME type into the table cell.
